and its algebras should satisfy the so-called Frobenius law. Then any\nmonad resolves as an adjunction, with extremal solutions given by the\ncategories of Kleisli and Frobenius-Eilenberg-Moore algebras, which again have\na dagger.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Apr 2019 13:27:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-25"}
